						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1305 (1383 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers gift of cows by <hi rend="bold">Sōmanāthadēva,</hi> son of <hi rend="italic">Pradhāni</hi> <hi rend="bold">Viṭṭappa,</hi> who was the son of <hi rend="bold">Apparasar</hi> of the Bhāradvāja-gōtra, for a perpetual lamp in the temple. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1305, Rudhirōdgārin, Kaṟkaṭaka, śu. 10, Monday, Hasta</hi> would correspond to A.D. <hi rend="bold">1383, July 6, Monday, if śu. 10.</hi> be emended into <hi rend="bold">śu 6.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
